data.shownotes: Before Head On/Pill, Stu asked the crowd "how about this one?" and teased the intro to Bone. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but no recordings are available. KGLW.net staff believes the setlist is complete based on contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlist@kglw.net.

Before Robot Stop, Stu said that they would be "trying something they had never really done before", referring to this being the first time the band performed the full Robot Stop through People-Vultures suite. After Trapdoor, Stu told the crowd that this was their first time in Indianapolis and asked if they had seen openers Chives and The Murlocs. Before Evil Death Roll, an audience member yelled out “you gotta play Road Train!” which Stu proceeded to tease. Thank you to ironchef for the full recording of this show.

KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist is likely incomplete. The full setlist for this show is unknown and there are no known audio or video recordings. The full Nonagon suite and Hot Wax were confirmed by an attendee. If anyone has any further information on what else was played at this show or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

After the Mind Fuzz suite, Stu told the crowd it was Cookie's 25th birthday, followed by the band singing “Happy Birthday to You” and Stu getting him to crowd surf for the first time. Before The River, an audience member requested Footy Footy, to which Joey asked if they even know what Australian football is. Head On/Pill contained Am I In Heaven? teases and quotes. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Robot Stop through Evil Death Roll were confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed through contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlist@kglw.net.

After Trapdoor, Stu briefly quoted Sleepwalker at the request of a fan. Before Robot Stop, Cavs teased Rock With You (Michael Jackson). During Big Fig Wasp, Joey picked Lucas up on his back, followed by his head hitting the ceiling and a piece immediately falling on the band. After Gamma Knife, Stu fought the piece of the ceiling that fell until it broke off, then started People-Vultures. Am I In Heaven contained Head On/Pill, Evil Death Roll and Hot Water teases.

Overkill (Motörhead) played before and as the band walked on stage. Twenty seconds into The River, the song was stopped and an attendee who was being removed by security was returned to the crowd at Stu's request. Head On/Pill contained Cellophane teases and quotes. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Robot Stop through People-Vultures and Cellophane through The River were confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed through contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlist@kglw.net.

KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. People-Vultures and Trapdoor were confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed through contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlist@kglw.net.

After Trapdoor, Joey commented that the venue "smells like [his] dad's breath, which is good!". After I'm In Your Mind Fuzz, Stu briefly teased Stressin'. Head On/Pill contained Robot Stop, Evil Death Roll, Hot Water and Big Fig Wasp teases, Cellophane and Am I In Heaven? teases and quotes and a flute solo. Thank you Michael Zelner for the full recording of this show.

Overkill (Motörhead) played as the band came on stage. During I'm Not In Your Mind, a camera recording the band fell over and Joey had to alert an audience member to bring it to a crew member. Head On/Pill featured Stu on flute and contained Robot Stop, Hot Water, Sea of Trees and Rattlesnake teases, as well as Cellophane and Am I In Heaven? teases and quotes. This show was recorded and released as the Live in San Francisco '16 album and concert film.

KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist may be incomplete. All songs were reported by an attendee and there are no known audio/video recordings. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

Willoughby's Beach was played for the first time known since 2015-06-27 (106 show gap). Wah Wah was played for the first time known since 2015-08-28 (83 show gap). Mr. Beat was not on the written setlist. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist is believed to be complete. Mr. Beat was confirmed by audio/video and the remaining songs were confirmed by a photo of the written setlist which is no longer available, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

Before Robot Stop, Cavs teased Rock With You (Michael Jackson), followed by Stu thanking Sam Joseph, Jason Galea and ORB as well as telling the audience that they were recording the show. The Lord of Lightning and The Balrog were introduced as new songs. Invisible Face was incomplete. The River contained Parts I, II, and IIIWah Wah contained The River teases. Thank you to Travis Kier for the complete recording

Between I’m In Your Mind Fuzz and Evil Death Roll Stu thanked the crowd in Portuguese. Invisible Face was incomplete. Only Part 1 of the The River was played. Wah-Wah contained quotes from The River. KGLW.net Staff Notes: We have attempted to clean up the audio to remove the overlapping audio from the end of Mind Fuzz and beginning of Evil Death Roll and minimize the hum throughout the recording.
The band played from 4:10-5:00pm
Band played from 9:10-10pm
Invisible Face was incomplete. Only Part I of The River was performed. Wah Wah contained The River quotes.
Matinee Show

Performed for NPR’s radio series, the World Cafe. It was recorded September 22nd, 2016 and aired January 25th, 2017. Following the performance, Stu was briefly interviewed and asked about the formation of the band.

This show was played at the Desert Daze Block Stage and featured lights by Mad Alchemy Liquid Light Show. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is likely incomplete and only partial recordings exist. Robot Stop, Big Fig Wasp and Cellophane have been verified by audio/video recording. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete/conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

This show featured the debuts of Greenhouse Heat Death, D-Day, The Book, Polygondwanaland, and The Fourth Colour. The vocal intro to Nuclear Fusion was not performed. All Is Known was played for the first time since 2018-02-18. (69 show gap) Doom City contained a Crumbling Castle outro. Evil Death Roll was played for the first time since 2017-06-06. (50 show gap) Big Fig Wasp was played for the first time since 2016-09-22. (100 show gap)

The Coffee Cola Song (Francis Bebey) played as the band came on stage. At the start of the show, Joey says this is "the biggest show we've ever played". Before Nuclear Fusion, Joey said that he had said he wasn't going to do the vocal intro anymore, but that he'd "do it tonight". He jokingly apologized to Sam after the vocal intro. The Book was instrumental. Doom City contained a Crumbling Castle outro. Sister Ray (The Velvet Underground) was played over the PA as the setbreak music with a 15 minute countdown on the screen. Han-Tyumi, The Confused Cyborg contained alternate lyrics and Stu on flute. Robot Stop contained a Hot Water tease.

Poster by Olya Dyer limited to 100 prints KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Big Fig Wasp was confirmed through video recording. The rest of the songs were confirmed via contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

This was the band's first show in Ireland, and took place at the historic Olympia Theatre (later known as 3Olympia Theatre for sponsorship purposes). The band was supported by Mild High Club. Alex Brettin from Mild High Club sat in during King Gizzard's set for D-Day and The Book. God Is In The Rhythm was played for the first time known since 2015-06-24. (241 show gap)

This show featured the debut of Beginner's Luck. Stu sat in on flute with opener Mild High Club on Sketches of Brunswick East II. Alex Brettin from Mild High Club played guitar for D-Day and The Book. Malcolm Brown (formerly of Whitney) played keyboard on Beginner's Luck.

This show featured the debut of Rock N’ Roll. On The Road Again (Rockets) played as the band came on stage. The vocal intro to Nuclear Fusion was not performed. Han-Tyumi, The Confused Cyborg contained alternate lyrics and Stu on flute. Before Rock N’ Roll, Joey had to gently kick a fan off the stage. Stu later mentioned that they were recording the show that night, and that the unreleased song (Rock N’ Roll) was "kinda new". A pro-shot video of The Fourth Colour was released on the Flightless Records YouTube channel. The Fourth Colour contained a tuning session outro with a droning noise playing in the background, and eventually Cellophane teases. Robot Stop contained Master of the Universe (Hawkwind) teases and quotes, and a Hot Water tease. Malcolm Brown (formerly of Whitney) played keyboard on Beginner's Luck. Stu sat in on flute with opener Mild High Club on Sketches of Brunswick East II.
King Khan performed improvised vocals over God Is In The Rhythm

“Electricity” (Captain Beefheart) played from the PA as the band came on stage. Doom City contained a Crumbling Castle outro. Han-Tyumi, The Confused Cyborg featured Stu on flute and alternate lyrics same as the KEXP performance. During the jam before Robot Stop, which contained The River, Am I In Heaven?, and Head On/Pill teases and quotes, Stu shouted out visual artist Jason Galea and wished him a happy birthday. Robot Stop contained a “Master Of The Universe” (Hawkwind) jam with lyrics. Poster by Carlo Vivary
Vomit Coffin was played for the first time since 2017-04-12. (82 show gap) Altered Beast I was played for the first time since 2017-04-18. (78 show gap)

“Whiplash” (Metallica) played as the band came on stage. Vomit Coffin and Alter Me I were incomplete. Before Rattlesnake, Stu shouted out Amyl & The Sniffers, the opening act. Greenhouse Heat Death contained a Sleep Drifter tease. Sleep Drifter contained a Rattlesnake tease. Billabong Valley contained a Sleep Drifter tease. After The Wheel, Joey said "That song was our Jerry Garcia attempt". The intro to Robot Stop contained Trapdoor, Cellophane, and Hot Water teases, and the song itself contained a Hot Water tease. At the end of the show, Joey shouted out the Golden State Warriors, the local NBA team, who were in the midst of the 2018 NBA finals series.

The intro to Robot Stop contained Cellophane and Head On/Pill teases. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but only partial recordings are available. Robot Stop through Big Fig Wasp, Rattlesnake, All Is Known through Digital Black and The Lord of Lightning through Crumbling Castle have been confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed by contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.
Poster by Sébastien Lépine
Altered Beast II was played for the first time since 2017-10-14. (53 show gap)
I'm In Your Mind was played for the first time since 2017-01-21. (133 shows) Alter Me II was played for the first time since 2017-12-02. (50 show gap)

KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist is likely incomplete. Rattlesnake through Gamma Knife were reported to have been performed, but no recordings are available. If anyone has any further information on what was played at this show or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but only partial recordings are available. Self-Immolate was confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed via the physical written setlist and contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net. Poster By Jason Galea Edition of 100

Evil Star was played through the PA speakers before and as the band went on stage. Robot Stop contained an Alter Me tease. The Bitter Boogie contained Cut Throat Boogie quotes and Cyboogie teases.

Poster By Jason Galea
Edition of 160

Evil Star was played through the PA speakers as the base came on stage. Robot stop contained Hot Water teases. There was a brief stop following Cyboogie due to an error in the PA system.

Poster By Jason Galea
Edition of 100

Work This Time contained a guitar solo. The intro to Robot Stop contained Hot Water and Rattlesnake teases. Alter Me and Altered Beast I were on the setlist after Muddy Water but cut for time. The Wheel through Float Along – Fill Your Lungs was released through the Official Bootlegger program as part of Live in Brussels ‘19. Poster By Jason Galea Edition of 400

Head On/Pill contained Rattlesnake quotes, Robot Stop, Venusuan 2 and The River teases and Hot Water, Am I In Heaven, Alter Me, and Cellophane teases and quotes, as well as guest performances from Stonefield and ORB members. Parts of the ‘Head On/Pill’ jam are featured in the ‘Chunky Shrapnel’ album. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist is believed to be complete. Most of Head On/Pill was confirmed by audio/video recording. The remaining songs were confirmed via contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net. Poster By Jason Galea Edition of 100

This was the Garage Rock Night show of the Princess Theatre residency, the fourth of five planned shows, each featuring a different specific genre and preannounced songs. This ended up being the final night of the residency as Metal Night, scheduled for December 23, 2021, was cancelled. The Lord of Lightning contained Cellophane teases. I’m Not In Your Mind contained Alter Me teases & quotes. Dead-Beat was played for the first time since 2015-06-26. (311 show gap) Black Tooth was played for the first time since 2015-09-13. (358 show gap) Wah Wah contained The River teases. Danger $$$ was played for the first time since 2018-10-04. (91 show gap) Muckraker was played for the first time since 2018-11-24. (84 show gap) Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases. Cut Throat Boogie was introduced as a song Ambrose wrote about the time Cookie bottled him. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete, but only partial recordings exist. Recordings of Digital Black are unavailable and most other songs are incomplete. The missing songs were confirmed based on the preannounced song lists for each of the 5 planned genre specific shows and contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net. Poster By Jason Galea Edition of 200

Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases.  Gamma Knife contained People-Vultures teases. Self-Immolate featured a drum solo by Cavs.  Her and I contained an Am I In Heaven? tease, Iron Lung quotes/teases, Slow Jam 1 quotes, Ice V teases and The River teases.

This show featured the debut of Sadie Sorceress.  Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases.  Sleep Drifter contained Honey, Rattlesnake and Automation teases. Honey contained Sleep Drifter and Automation teases. Planet B was introduced as a song about capitalism. Han-Tyumi’s vocals in the MOTU suite were performed in Spanish.

Third of five nights in Barcelona for Primavera Sound. Second show with replacement guitars for Stu's Holy Explorer & Joey's Flying V. Robot Stop contained The Dripping Tap teases and quotes. K.G.L.W (Intro) and Doom City were written on the printed setlist but were not played. KGLW.net Staff Notes: The setlist for this show is believed to be complete. Robot Stop through Gamma Knife have been confirmed via audio/video recordings. The remaining songs were confirmed via contemporaneous discussions through various social media, but any additional setlist notations that require audio confirmation (guest appearances, segues, quotes or teases) may be incomplete. If anyone has any further information or, ideally, a complete or conclusive recording please contact KGLW.net staff at setlists@kglw.net.

This show featured the debut of Red Smoke.  Gaia featured a Cavs drum solo over a metal vamp from the band. Leah Senior was shouted out after Hot Water.  Hot Water was reprised during Robot Stop. Work This Time featured a guitar solo.

Poster By Carlo Vivary

Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases and The Dripping Tap teases/quotes. Hot Water had lyrics changed to “time to party”. Persistence contained Sleepwalker teases. Hypertension contained Ice V teases/quotes. Sadie Sorceress was introduced as a song about Amby’s nana and contained a Crumbling Castle tease and an extra verse from The Grim Reaper. Shanghai was dedicated to orange juice and featured a Grow Wings and Fly 'Lets Get Real High' jam with dub keyboard elements highly reminiscent of The Scientist’s Butterfly 3001 Shanghai remix. Magenta Mountain had lyrics changed to “I don’t believe Stu”. Mars For the Rich was listed on the written setlist after Planet B but was not played. Gaia featured a drum solo by Cavs, during which Amby and Stu laid down on the stage to watch. Poster By Mr. Joe Johnson

Gaia contained Motor Spirit teases/quotes and featured a drum solo by Cavs. Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases and The Dripping Tap teases/quotes. Hot Water contained The Dripping Tap teases and had lyrics changed to "time to party". The segue from Gamma Knife to Hypertension consisted of a full band outro of People-Vultures. Work This Time contained an “Incredible” (M Beat) quote. Work This Time contained a guitar solo. Shanghai featured a Grow Wings and Fly jam. Amby shouted out Tame Impala after Shanghai. The Grim Reaper featured an additional verse from Sadie Sorceress and contained Horology teases. The Dripping Tap contained Am I in Heaven? teases, Cellophane teases, Head On/Pill teases, and a jam reminiscent of Mycelium.

This show featured the debut of Supercell. The Dripping Tap contained Hot Water teases and Hypertension teases. Robot Stop contained The Dripping Tap teases. Gamma Knife and People-Vultures contained Motor Spirit teases/quotes. Iron Lung contained Hypertension teases. Hypertension contained Witchcraft teases, Hot Water teases, and Robot Stop teases. KGLW.net Staff Notes: Special shout out to our very own @28rebounds for the recording located on Archive.org! Poster By Jason Galea 215 Standard / 80 Foil Print

This show featured the debuts of Motor Spirit and Hate Dancin’. Gaia featured a drum solo by Cavs. Motor Spirit was incomplete. Sense contained Am I In Heaven? teases, Iron Lung quotes, Head On/Pill teases, and a Straws in the Wind vocal jam with “no sense at all” vocals. The Grim Reaper featured “I’m the Shrimp Reaper” vocals and contained Torture Chamber quotes. Following Astroturf, Cavs’ parents briefly appeared on stage. Down the Sink was played for the first time since May 24, 2022 (70 show gap) and had lyrics changed to “the street is where people jam.” Robot Stop contained Hot Water and The Dripping Tap teases and quotes, an Extinction quote, and a proto-Grow Wings and Fly jam. Gamma Knife contained Motor Spirit teases. Iron Lung contained Sense teases. Poster By Jason Galea 1200 Standard / 300 Foil Prints

Robot Stop contained a Hot Water jam with lyrics and Evil Death Roll teases. Hypertension contained Hot Water teases. This Thing contained a quote of “Walkin’ on the Sun” (Smash Mouth). Slow Jam 1 contained Iron Lung quotes. Poster by Michael Hacker

data.jamchart_notes: first time played not following Robot Stop, contained RS outro as intro
data.shownotes:
The intro to O.N.E. contained a Straws in The Wind tease. The Book was played for the first time since 2023-03-07	(82 show gap). Gaia contained a You Can Be Your Sillhouette tease and featured a drum solo. Plastic Boogie was played for the first time since 2023-06-13 (55 show gap). This Thing contained The Dripping Tap teases and a Hell's Itch tease. Slow Jam 1 and Sense featured Ambrose on sax. Before Field of Vision, the band pretended like they were going to play Hog Calling Contest but they did a jam loosely based on it with lyrics based on the movie The Mask. Big Fig Wasp contained the ending of Robot Stop as the intro. The intro to People-Vultures and the song itself contained Iron Lung jams with lyrics. Iron Lung contained a People-Vultures jam with lyrics.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard Edition - 600
Foil Edition - 150

Robot Stop featured Ambrose on saxophone and contained Sad Pilot, Converge, and Witchcraft teases. Gamma Knife contained a Motor Spirit tease. People-Vultures contained Iron Lung teases & quotes. Mr. Beat contained Sad Pilot teases. Sad Pilot was introduced as a song about donkeys and dedicated to band soundman Joe Santarpia.  Rats in the Sky was introduced as a song about chickens in the sky. Cut Throat Boogie contained The Bitter Boogie teases and was dedicated to Magic Sam. You Can Be Your Silhouette was dedicated to Alex Brettin of Mild High Club, who then briefly appeared on stage. The Fourth Colour contained quotes of Gila Monster and Mars For the Rich. Straws In the Wind contained a Rattlesnake quote. Welcome to An Altered Future was played for the first time since 2018-03-16. (304 show gap) This was also the first time the suite was performed in full. Set featured Joey on guitar and Ambrose on saxophone. Head On/Pill was not on the written setlist and featured Ambrose on saxophone and contained Am I In Heaven? and Robot Stop teases, Chang'e teases and quotes, and a Hot Water jam with lyrics. At the end of the show, Ambrose thanked Chicago for The Blues Brothers and blues music.

Poster by Jason Galea
Standard Edition - 1200
Foil Edition - 300
data.venuename: Huntington Bank Pavilion at Northerly Island

data.shownotes: Slow Jam 1 contained Crumbling Castle and Am I In Heaven? teases. This Thing contained Am I In Heaven? teases and quotes. Am I In Heaven? contained The Land Before Timeland, Whole Lotta Rosie (AC/DC) and Witchcraft teases and a Slow Jam 1 jam with lyrics, and featured improvised alternate lyrics. Self-Immolate featured a drum solo by Cavs. Nuclear Fusion featured community taper Mystery Jack for the vocal intro. Hog Calling Contest was teased prior to Antarctica, which contained Am I In Heaven? teases. Boogieman Sam contained La Grange (ZZ Top) teases and a Riff Raff (AC/DC) jam. Following Boogieman Sam, Joey mentioned that the band would be performing at the Hollywood Bowl with the L.A. Philharmonic on their upcoming tour in 2025, which was previously unannounced at the time. Texas Flood and Pride and Joy (Stevie Ray Vaughan) were teased prior to Daily Blues, which contained Hot Water teases. Robot Stop contained Hot Water teases, This Thing quotes, Forty Six and 2 (Tool) teases and Master of the Universe (Hawkwind) teases and quotes. Gamma Knife was unfinished. Ice V contained The Lord of Lightning teases. The Lord of Lightning contained Cellophane teases. Le Risque featured Jay Weinberg on drums. Additionally, Cavs got an audience member to perform a laugh for the song and brought Jay's wife Chloe on stage to perform the 'Let's Ride' vocal part. Following Le Risque, Amby quoted I Love L.A. (Randy Newman).

Hot Water featured Ambrose on sax. Raw Feel contained a Muddy Water tease and was unfinished. Muddy Water featured Ambrose on sax and contained The Bitter Boogie teases. The Bitter Boogie also featured Ambrose on sax and contained Muddy Water teases as well as an outro jam with lyrics. Gilgamesh contained Magenta Mountain teases and quotes and was unfinished. Before Billabong Valley Ambrose quoted Hits From the Bong (Cypress Hill).  The Great Chain of Being contained The Bitter Boogie teases.
